  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Global Programme: Enhancing Readmission and Legal Identity Capacity (RELICA)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Today, approximately 1 billion of the global population still live without legal identity and remain invisible for states. The implications of this global identity gap are far-reaching: ordinary day-to-day services such as education, health care, opening a bank account, paying taxes, as well as the right to vote, or to migrate regularly are inaccessible without a legal identity. The project aims at establishing and/or strengthening robust legal identity systems in Iraq, Rwanda and Cabo Verde to lay the fundamental groundworks to facilitate the global roll-out of eRCMS and enhance right-based return management. eRCMS systems have flexibility to establish links between agencies and databases and may therefore support states&apos; legal identity capacities through a phased approach depending on the varied needs and context of individual states. Implementation of the eRCMS system may not only enhances legal identity capacity but concurrently also addresses related readmission challenges, nationally as well as globally.</narrative>
  </description>
